    {
      "title": "AILogAnalyzer — Multi-Agent JVM Diagnostics Platform",
      "description": "Designed an 8-agent orchestration platform using Google ADK and Java 17 that analyzes live microservice logs across Ecommerce, Finance, and Health domains in real time, ingesting from 4 Kafka topics and JMX MBean counters to detect latency spikes, deadlocks, memory leaks, and session conflicts.\nEngineered OrchestratorAgent with parallel ExecutorService dispatch per 500ms micro-batch, reducing pipeline analysis latency from O(n agents) to O(1 slowest agent) achieving sub-second anomaly detection at scale with MemoryAgent’s heap leak signal recognition and GC-thrash pattern detection.\nApplied domain-driven alert severity, Finance data conflicts escalate to FATAL (regulatory/double-spend risk), Health latency thresholds tightened by 40% for patient-facing SLAs routing each alert type to sector-specific remediation pipelines via Kafka.",
      "longDescription": "Designed an 8-agent orchestration platform using Google ADK and Java 17 that analyzes live microservice logs across Ecommerce, Finance, and Health domains in real time, ingesting from 4 Kafka topics and JMX MBean counters to detect latency spikes, deadlocks, memory leaks, and session conflicts.\nEngineered OrchestratorAgent with parallel ExecutorService dispatch per 500ms micro-batch, reducing pipeline analysis latency from O(n agents) to O(1 slowest agent) achieving sub-second anomaly detection at scale with MemoryAgent’s heap leak signal recognition and GC-thrash pattern detection.\nApplied domain-driven alert severity, Finance data conflicts escalate to FATAL (regulatory/double-spend risk), Health latency thresholds tightened by 40% for patient-facing SLAs routing each alert type to sector-specific remediation pipelines via Kafka.",
