      "title": "AIFitro — AI-Powered Fitness Tracking Platform",
      "description": "Architected a cloud-native microservices platform using Spring Boot, Spring Cloud Gateway (WebFlux), Eureka service discovery, and Keycloak (OAuth2 PKCE) enabling stateless authentication, token-based authorization, and secure service-to service communication.\nDesigned an event-driven Kafka pipeline with MongoDB persistence supporting ~10K req/min, with idempotency controls and DLQ retry logic ensuring reliable data processing with zero message loss across distributed services.\nBuilt a React + Redux frontend with real-time analytics dashboards integrated with backend REST APIs, deployed via Docker and Kubernetes with Jenkins CI/CD pipelines for automated build, test, and release cycles.",
      "longDescription": "Architected a cloud-native microservices platform using Spring Boot, Spring Cloud Gateway (WebFlux), Eureka service discovery, and Keycloak (OAuth2 PKCE) enabling stateless authentication, token-based authorization, and secure service-to service communication.\nDesigned an event-driven Kafka pipeline with MongoDB persistence supporting ~10K req/min, with idempotency controls and DLQ retry logic ensuring reliable data processing with zero message loss across distributed services.\nBuilt a React + Redux frontend with real-time analytics dashboards integrated with backend REST APIs, deployed via Docker and Kubernetes with Jenkins CI/CD pipelines for automated build, test, and release cycles.",
